title: Rede de fast-food inaugura nova loja na região de Ribeirão e abre vagas de emprego
text:
O McDonald’s vai inaugurar uma nova unidade em Cravinhos, na região de Ribeirão Preto, e está com 30 vagas de emprego abertas para o cargo de atendente de restaurante. As oportunidades são voltadas a pessoas com ou sem deficiência e não exigem experiência anterior.
Para participar da seleção, os candidatos devem estar cursando ou já ter concluído o Ensino Médio.
Entre os benefícios oferecidos estão:
- Vale-transporte
- Plano de saúde e odontológico
- Alimentação no restaurante
- Wellhub
- Seguro de vida
- Programas de saúde e bem-estar
- Participação nos resultados
- Plano de carreira
Além disso, os contratados passam a integrar um programa de capacitação e desenvolvimento profissional, que contempla a formação técnica e comportamental.
Os interessados devem entrar em contato pelo WhatsApp (16) 99302-8297 para obter mais informações e participar do processo seletivo.

author: Andie Reeves
title: Turkey converts seized biker gang supercars into incredible $4 million police fleet
text:
In Turkey, you can now get pulled over for speeding by a Bugatti.
The traffic department’s fleet just got stocked with some incredible luxury cars.
Seeing a policeman driving a Porsche is one thing, learning how they got these cars is a whole other story.
READ MORE:
Woman orders an Uber in Austria and gets picked up by epic supercar
Turkey is giving the
Dubai Police fleet a run for its money.
Ali Yerlikaya, the country’s interior minister, made a
post on X announcing several new additions to the traffic departments’ garage.
The Turkish Police Department led a massive raid where they impounded several sports cars, supercars and SUVs.
The luxury SUVs included a Range Rover Sport and a Mercedes-Benz GLS.
A Ferrari 458 and a Bentley Continental were some of the more expensive cars they nabbed.
There were also some performance cars such as a Porsche Taycan and a Volkswagen Golf R.
In total, there were 23 cars, with a combined value of $3.5 million.
The vehicles came from one source: a drug trafficker called Hakan Ayik.
Once described as “Australia’s most wanted man”, Ayik has an estimated fortune of $1 billion.
Police arrested him and 36 of his cronies in Istanbul last month, and discovered their incredible car collection while doing so.
After the vehicles were seized, the court decided to gift them back to the team that led the successful sting.
Now every car has been transformed into a police cruiser.
“From now on, these tools do not belong to criminal organizations,” Yerlikaya said.
“It will be at the disposal of our police and at the service of our Nation!”
This puts Turkey up there with some of the coolest police fleets in the world.
In Qatar police cruise around in a
Lamborghini Urus.
While the
Dubai Police Force has a Bentley Continental GT V8 in its luxury lineup.
It also has the Ghiath, an
ultra-futuristic car with 12 secret cameras and its own drone.

author: MoneyDJ新聞
title: 工研院攜法國Saft 開發磷酸錳鐵鋰電池技術
text: MoneyDJ新聞 2025-07-03 11:52:59 記者 新聞中心 報導工研院今(3)日表示，全球電池技術領導廠商法國Saft公司技術長Dr. Nechev日前拜訪工研院，並在台灣泓辰材料(HCM)董事長陳宏力見證之下，雙方正式簽署合作協議。工研院將運用泓辰材料公司所開發的高性能磷酸錳鐵鋰(LMFP)粉體正極材料，攜手法國Saft公司開發新一代LMFP電池技術，搶攻電動車與儲能系統市場，也展現台灣在高階電池材料領域的研發實力與產業價值。 LMFP電池為傳統磷酸鐵鋰(LFP)電池的升級版本，除延續其低成本、長壽命與高安全性等特性外，電壓與能量密度更提高約15~20%，成為未來電動車與儲能系統的關鍵技術。此次台法合作將促進材料與電池技術的深度整合，為全球新能源應用帶來更具競爭力的解決方案。 工研院材料與化工研究所所長邱國展表示，此次與Saft的合作，是台灣電池材料技術進軍國際市場的重要里程碑，將結合雙方優勢，共同推動LMFP電池的技術驗證與商品化，創造國際合作新典範。 Saft技術長Dr. Nechev亦對台灣在電池材料創新上的表現表示高度肯定，期待透過本次合作強化Saft在新一代電池技術的全球布局。 此合作不僅拓展國際夥伴關係，更將帶動台灣電池產業鏈整體升級與市場拓展，為邁向淨零排放與永續發展目標注入新動能。

text:
A prática regular de exercícios físicos é essencial para manter uma vida saudável e equilibrada. Dentre as diversas opções disponíveis para a prática de atividade física, as esteiras elétricas tornaram-se populares pela conveniência, versatilidade e eficácia. A Esteira Eletrônica Dream Fitness Concept 2.5 é um exemplo notável dessa categoria, destacando-se por seus recursos avançados e qualidade de construção.
A Importância dos Exercícios Físicos
Antes de explorarmos os benefícios específicos da Esteira Dream Fitness Concept 2.5, é crucial entender por que a prática regular de exercícios físicos é fundamental para a saúde geral. A inatividade física está associada a uma série de problemas de saúde, incluindo obesidade, doenças cardíacas, diabetes e até mesmo distúrbios mentais como ansiedade e depressão.
Ao se engajar em atividades físicas, como o uso de uma esteira elétrica, os benefícios vão além da simples queima de calorias. A prática regular melhora a resistência cardiovascular, fortalece os músculos, promove a flexibilidade e contribui para a saúde mental. Além disso, a liberação de endorfinas durante o exercício ajuda a reduzir o estresse e melhorar o humor.
Esteira Eletrônica Dream Fitness Concept 2.5: Uma Visão Geral
A Esteira Eletrônica Dream Fitness Concept 2.5 destaca-se como uma opção robusta para aqueles que desejam integrar exercícios físicos em sua rotina diária. Equipada com recursos avançados, essa esteira oferece uma experiência de treino eficaz e confortável.
1. Design Ergonômico:
A Dream Fitness Concept 2.5 é projetada com um foco especial no conforto do usuário. Sua superfície de corrida acolchoada reduz o impacto nas articulações, tornando-a ideal para pessoas de todas as idades. O design dobrável facilita o armazenamento em espaços compactos, tornando-a uma escolha prática para ambientes domésticos.
2. Motor Potente:
Equipada com um motor potente, esta esteira oferece uma ampla faixa de velocidades e inclinações ajustáveis. Isso permite que os usuários personalizem seus treinos de acordo com seus objetivos, seja para queima de gordura, aumento de resistência ou treinos de alta intensidade.
3. Painel de Controle Intuitivo:
O painel de controle da Dream Fitness Concept 2.5 é intuitivo e fácil de usar. Ele fornece informações em tempo real sobre a distância percorrida, calorias queimadas, tempo de exercício e outras métricas relevantes. A presença de programas de treino pré-definidos adiciona variedade aos treinos, mantendo os usuários motivados.
4. Conectividade Tecnológica:
A esteira oferece conectividade Bluetooth, permitindo que os usuários sincronizem seus dispositivos e controlem o treino por meio de aplicativos específicos. Essa funcionalidade moderna integra a tecnologia ao exercício, proporcionando uma experiência interativa e personalizada.
Benefícios da Esteira Dream Fitness Concept 2.5:
1. Queima de Calorias e Controle de Peso:
A queima de calorias durante o uso da esteira contribui significativamente para o controle de peso. A capacidade de ajustar a intensidade do treino torna a Dream Fitness Concept 2.5 eficaz tanto para iniciantes quanto para atletas mais experientes.
2. Melhoria da Saúde Cardiovascular:
A prática regular de exercícios aeróbicos, como correr na esteira, fortalece o sistema cardiovascular. Isso resulta em uma melhoria na circulação sanguínea, redução da pressão arterial e menor risco de doenças cardíacas.
3. Fortalecimento Muscular:
A inclinação ajustável da esteira simula terrenos variados, desafiando diferentes grupos musculares. Isso contribui para o fortalecimento global do corpo, incluindo pernas, glúteos e músculos centrais.
4. Promoção do Bem-Estar Mental:
Além dos benefícios físicos, a prática regular de exercícios físicos, como os oferecidos pela Esteira Dream Fitness Concept 2.5, promove a liberação de endorfinas, melhorando o humor, reduzindo o estresse e contribuindo para a saúde mental.
Conclusão:
Investir em uma esteira elétrica de qualidade, como a Dream Fitness Concept 2.5, é mais do que uma escolha
bora de fitness de conveniência. É um compromisso com a saúde e o bem-estar. Ao incorporar exercícios físicos regulares em nossa rotina, colhemos uma série de benefícios que impactam positivamente todos os aspectos de nossa vida. A Dream Fitness Concept 2.5 não apenas proporciona uma plataforma eficaz para alcançar esses benefícios, mas também torna a jornada do fitness mais acessível e motivadora. Portanto, ao buscar uma vida saudável e ativa, a Dream Fitness Concept 2.5 se destaca como uma escolha notável no universo das esteiras elétricas

author: Kyeland Jackson
title: January assault on elderly man turns deadly, marking eighth homicide in St. Paul
text:
A teenager has been charged with manslaughter for punching a 76-year-old man at Harriet Island Park in St. Paul in January, causing his death from complications of the injury weeks later.
Prosecutors with the Ramsey County Attorney's Office charged Wyatt Doerfler, 18, with first-degree manslaughter. Doerfler's next court date is May 1.
Doerfler is believed to have punched Thomas Dunne on Jan. 28, damaging his right eye. Despite surgery and treatment, infection spread from Dunne's wound and he was pronounced dead weeks later. The Ramsey County Medical Examiner ruled Dunne's death was a homicide likely caused by complications from that assault.
Doerfler was originally charged with first-degree assault, but prosecutors upgraded it to manslaughter after Dunne's death.
"After receiving additional investigation from law enforcement, including the medical examiner's report, we amended the juvenile petition to include a charge of Manslaughter in the 1st Degree – the highest charge we could prove beyond a reasonable doubt in court," Ramsey County Attorney's Office spokesman Dennis Gerhardstein said in a statement.
According to charging documents:
Police responded to Harriet Island Park around 5 p.m. for a reported assault. Dunne was waiting there as blood flowed from his right eye. He said he was in the park when a man began urinating in public. Dunne said he took out his phone to take a picture but two people exited a car nearby and tried to take the phone away. Dunne said one of those men punched his face.
A witness interviewed by police said the men slapped Dunne's phone from his hand before punching him two times in the face. The witness reportedly yelled at the men, who walked away. Officers found the group of men that day and arrested Doerfler. He declined to provide a statement after his arrest, but answered "yeah, that was me" when officers asked if someone from their group was involved in a fight.
A man from the group, identified in charging documents as "L.R.G.", said they confronted Dunne because they believed he was recording him. Dunne, L.R.G. said, should have "minded his business." Another member of the group said they started urinating in the pond because they could not find a restroom. He stated that Doerfler said, "Let's get to it" before punching Dunne.
Dunne was evaluated at Regions Hospital that day. After emergency surgery, staff reported that Dunne suffered facial fractures and traumatic damage to his right eye that could erase most of his vision. He was discharged the next day but returned on Feb. 3 with complications. He contracted an infection that worsened, forcing Dunne onto a ventilator before he was pronounced dead Feb. 23.
According to his online obituary , Dunne, of St. Paul, was born in Ireland and immigrated to the United States with his family at age 2. He was a member of the Marine Corps who served two tours in Vietnam. In addition to being a decorated veteran, he was "a wonderful chef, prolific writer, playwright, acted in amateur theater, licensed pilot, active in his community as a Board member of his Condominium Association and in that role he campaigned for security cameras in Skywalk public spaces." He was also a member of Mensa. He is survived by his wife, Helen Broderick.
Dunne's death marks the eighth homicide in St. Paul this year. There were a dozen by this time last year, according to a Star Tribune database.

author: Ronny Lerner, NCA Newswire
title: A-League 2023: Brisbane Roar coach Luciano Trani’s stunning Melbourne City spray after 8-1cdefeat
text:
Melbourne City fire 8 GOALS against Roar | 02:30 Ronny Lerner, NCA Newswire from Code Sports December 29th, 2023 8:44 am Interim Brisbane Roar coach Luciano Trani believes the advantages that the well-resourced Melbourne City has over other A-League clubs are unfair.
Speaking after his first game in charge of the Roar, which resulted in a record-equalling 8-1 destruction at the hands of City, Trani described his vanquishers as a “global corporation”.
City are owned by the City Football Group which boasts English giants Manchester City, La Liga side Girona and MLS club New York City in its stable amongst other clubs from around the world.
“They have resources beyond what an A-League club is and I understand that because I’ve been there and I know what the resources and facilities are,” said Trani who was a former assistant coach with Melbourne City.
“They are a quality club that have all bases covered and it’s credit for them.
Stumped to gift ideas? This festive season, give the gift that keeps on giving. Gift a Kayo subscription from just $25 a month!
Curtis Good celebrates a goal during City’s record-equalling thrashing of Brisbane Roar. Picture: Getty Source: Getty Images
“But I look at it from a Brisbane Roar point of view and I’ve come here understanding that the challenges are there.
“Yes, the league has 12 teams, but within the 12 teams there is quite a bit going on between what some other teams have got and what teams maybe are limited to.
“I think it’s important to put into true context of this.
“They can call on resources globally to assist their program and so therefore you’re not up against one or two individuals, you’re up against a team and a club that’s been modelled around getting the right message across, details that are across all levels at the highest level.”
Melbourne City celebrate the 2021 title during their powerhouse run. Picture: AFP Source: AFP
Trani admitted it would be hard to get his players up for their next game against Sydney FC at Suncorp Stadium next week, but stressed they had no other choice.
“It’s challenging, yes. It’s not easy but I think it’s why we’re footballers and we’re involved in the game,” he said.
“We have to remind ourselves that we have to back up a performance and improve from where we left off, and the only thing is you’ve got to bounce back.
“Setbacks are going to happen in the world of football and it’s just one of those weeks where now we have to show what type of people we are and what characters and personalities we have in order for us to continue and move forward.”
Despite having now conceded 13 goals in their last three matches, which have all been losses, Trani was steadfast on implementing an attacking, risk-taking brand of football.
“We have made a conscious decision that we’re going to continue to play this way,” he said.
“So, whether it’s hard-headed or whether it’s wrong or whether it’s right, we believe that if we want to get a football team that wants to enjoy football, we have to be on the front foot.
“It’s going to be on the edge, but that’s the way it’s going to have to be or else...”
